Description: Babel Vienna. The two large ships in the foreground on the right. Bruegel used them for drawings which were also used for the ship series, but the sails are rolled up - the boats are in harbour: 1) the boat on the right, cf. Nef de Bande, Bast.100 with one man climbing up the "Takelage" and another on a pole at the end of the ship - identical the same ship again in Icarus and reversed in the left foreground of Naples; 2) the other boat strongly foreshortened central of three ships in Bast.104, also Bast. 106.
